<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="6Nov1922"><font color="red">6 November 1922</font>, <cite>BLHW</cite> (JJ to Harriet Weaver, dictated): Miss Beach sent me Criterion so will you please send the copy you meant for me to Mrs M[&mdash;] (Group A). Mr Larbaud's article reads very well. It is a relief after recent criticisms to meet a man who knows what he wants to say, knows how to say it and says it. The touch (of) at the end of the second last paragraph is very neat. It will flatter English crtics too as coming from a Frenchman. <br>P.S. Errata p.37 li 2 from foot &hellip; Divid better A catalectic <br>&hellip; join better march ing</div>
